casebody.data:
STATE
v.
HILL 2019-0409 Supreme Court of Ohio. April 23, 2019

MISCELLANEOUS DISMISSAL

Appellee/cross-appellant, Genesis Hill, has not filed a memorandum in response and in support of cross-appeal, due April 19, 2019, in compliance with the Rules of Practice of the Supreme Court of Ohio and therefore has failed to prosecute this cause with the requisite diligence. Cross-appeal dismissed. The appeal of appellant/cross-appellee, the state of Ohio, remains pending.
